defs.docs:
Laminar is a semi-reliable UDP-based protocol for multiplayer games. This library implements wrappers around the UDP-protocol,
 and provides a lightweight, message-based interface which provides certain guarantees like reliability and ordering.

defs.name: Config
defs.value: Config { idle_connection_timeout, max_packet_size, max_fragments, fragment_size, fragment_reassembly_buffer_size, receive_buffer_max_size, rtt_smoothing_factor, rtt_max_value, socket_event_buffer_size, socket_polling_timeout }
defs.docs: Contains the configuration options to configure laminar for special use-cases.

defs.name: idle_connection_timeout
defs.docs: Value which can specify the amount of time that can pass without hearing from a client before considering them disconnected

defs.name: max_packet_size
defs.docs: Value which can specify the maximum size a packet can be in bytes. This value is inclusive of fragmenting; if a packet is fragmented, the total size of the fragments cannot exceed this value.

defs.name: max_fragments
defs.docs: Value which can specify the maximal allowed fragments.

defs.name: fragment_size
defs.docs: Value which can specify the size of a fragment.

defs.name: fragment_reassembly_buffer_size
defs.docs: Value which can specify the size of the buffer that queues up fragments ready to be reassembled once all fragments have arrived.```

defs.name: receive_buffer_max_size
defs.docs: Value that specifies the size of the buffer the UDP data will be read into. Defaults to `1450` bytes.

defs.name: rtt_smoothing_factor
defs.docs: Value which can specify the factor which will smooth out network jitter.

defs.name: rtt_max_value
defs.docs: Value which can specify the maximal round trip time (rtt) for packet.

defs.name: socket_event_buffer_size
defs.docs: Value which can specify the event buffer we read socket events into.

defs.name: socket_polling_timeout
defs.docs: Value which can specify how long we should block polling for socket events.

defs.name: Socket
defs.docs: A reliable UDP socket implementation with configurable reliability and ordering guarantees.

defs.name: bind
defs.docs:
Binds to the socket and then sets up `ActiveConnections` to manage the "connections".
 Because UDP connections are not persistent, we can only infer the status of the remote
 endpoint by looking to see if they are still sending packets or not
